{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17597760","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17597760"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:28:53+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:28:53+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15428"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15428","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15428"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.66,0.28,0.03,0.03,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8119"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65930"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8119","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8119"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15428"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51376"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"},{"type":"tags","id":"8412"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19688"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19694"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22027"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65930","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65930"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe gallbladder wall contains several distinct layers including the mucosa, muscularis, and serosa.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the arrangement of the muscularis layer?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Inner circular and outer longitudinal smooth muscle layers","Inner longitudinal and outer circular smooth muscle layers","Irregular smooth muscle fibres without distinct layers","Three distinct layers of smooth muscle","Striated muscle fibres in a circular arrangement"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe gallbladder wall has a unique muscular arrangement. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eirregular smooth muscle fibres without distinct layers\u003C/strong\u003E allow for controlled contraction during bile release. This differs from the typical gastrointestinal tract arrangement of \u003Cstrong\u003Einner circular and outer longitudinal smooth muscle layers\u003C/strong\u003E seen in the small intestine and most of the digestive tract.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe suggestion of \u003Cstrong\u003Einner longitudinal and outer circular smooth muscle layers\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as this is the reverse of the normal gut arrangement. The presence of \u003Cstrong\u003Ethree distinct layers of smooth muscle\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as this arrangement is found in the stomach but not the gallbladder. \u003Cstrong\u003EStriated muscle fibres\u003C/strong\u003E are not present in the gallbladder - smooth muscle is the only type found in this organ.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The gallbladder wall contains an irregular arrangement of smooth muscle fibres without distinct layers.","This structure differs from the typical three-layered arrangement found in most of the gastrointestinal tract."],"references":["Jones MW, Small K, Kashyap S, et al. Physiology, Gallbladder. [Updated 2023 May 1]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482488/","Nightingale, J. M. (2012). Applied anatomy and physiology of the gastrointestinal tract (GIT). Gastrointestinal Tract Imaging E-Book: Gastrointestinal Tract Imaging E-Book, 45.","Podolsky, D. K., Camilleri, M., Fitz, J. G., Kalloo, A. N., Shanahan, F., \u0026 Wang, T. C. (Eds.). (2015). Yamada\u0027s textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons.","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51376"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15428"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51376","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51376"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-27T17:21:23+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-27T17:21:41+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8119"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65930"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4928","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4928"},"attributes":{"emoji":"